WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
If you've ever tried to build or fix a GTFS feed, you know it can be painful.

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:13.000
Tedious shape editing, Python scripts, spreadsheets, and lots of those validation errors.

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:22.000
Enter GTFS·X, a fast, easy, browser-based editor that makes editing a breeze.

00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:27.000
It handles the spec correctly as you build routes, stops, and schedules all on a map.

00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:36.000
Draw a route by snapping lines to streets, drop stops where they belong, add a service calendar, and easily generate timed runs.

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:42.000
When you're done, export a standards-compliant GTFS zip in one click.

00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:47.000
Continuous validation flags errors as you edit, before you export.

00:00:47.000 --> 00:00:50.000
Upgrading to Pro adds hosted publishing.

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:57.000
Your feed lives at a canonical URL, so Google Maps or your CAD/AVL vendor can just consume it.

00:00:57.000 --> 00:01:03.000
Snapshot history and Mobility Database submission are all included.

00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:07.000
Give it a try for free at gtfsx.com.

00:01:07.000 --> 00:01:12.000
No sign-up required — just open the editor and start.
